## UI Conventions (All Dashboard Apps)

### Header Pattern
```
<header> with linear-gradient background using app accent color
  - Uppercase tracking-wide label (app name)
  - Large Space Grotesk title
  - Subtitle paragraph
  - Pill-style links to all ecosystem apps + GitHub + Blog
</header>
```

### Nav Pattern
```
Sticky top-0 z-50 nav with glass blur background
  Tab buttons with tab-btn / tab-btn-active classes
```

### Scenario Pattern (Best → Worst)
All apps use 4 scenarios with interactive toggle:
- **Aggressive/Best** — green `#10b981`
- **Moderate** — sky `#38bdf8`
- **Business as Usual** — amber `#f59e0b`
- **Worst Case** — rose `#f43f5e`

Each scenario card has: icon, name, description. Active scenario gets `ring-2` + glow.

TransitionOS exception: uses 3 scenarios (Baseline, Transition OS, Full Stack) with colors `#64748b`, `#38bdf8`, `#34d399`.

### Score Panel Pattern
Every app's Overview tab starts with a "Today's Score" panel:
- Circular SVG progress ring with letter grade + numeric score
- Grid of sub-domain cards with grades, trend arrows, notes
- Domain scores are scenario-aware (update when scenario changes)

### Chart Pattern
- Recharts `AreaChart` with all scenario lines
- Active scenario: `strokeWidth={3}`, full opacity
- Inactive: `strokeWidth={1.5}`, `strokeOpacity={0.35}`
- Gradient fills with `linearGradient` defs
- **Each chart gets a scenario-aware descriptive paragraph beneath it**
- **Each chart section gets a comprehensive summary at the bottom**

### Footer Pattern
```
Links to all ecosystem apps with emoji + name
GitHub link
Centered, small text
```

